  "analyst_note": "CVE-2017-12542: Authentication bypass by sending 29+ 'Connection' headers in HP iLO4 < 2.53. CVSS 9.8. Allows unauthenticated access to the iLO REST API, enabling full server compromise including BIOS flashing. iLO servers typically respond with 'Server: HP-iLO-Server/1.30' or similar. Port 443 (HTTPS) is the standard iLO web interface; port 17988 is sometimes used for iLO Remote Console. If iLO is accessible from the internet, this is critical \u2014 iLO should NEVER be internet-facing. Fixed: iLO 4 v2.53.",
